<title type="html"><![CDATA[Is there an option to NOT remember folders view settings?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=193&amp;p=841#p841"><![CDATA[
When navigating around in folders, I'll change the folder I'm in to &quot;Detailed View&quot; but then click into another one and it will switch to &quot;Icon View&quot;. The little research I did told me that in XP there was an option to <em>not</em> &quot;Remember Each Folders View Settings&quot; but it was removed in Vista/Win7. Does Classic Shell for Explorer have an option to disable this function? If not, is it a feature that can be added in a future release? Thanks.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=257">vgpclife</a> — Mon Feb 04, 2013 8:34 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
